urity/2021/05/10/beware-of-applications-misusing-root-stores/):\n\n> **Correctly using Root Stores**: Curating a root store is a costly ongoing responsibility, so the [Common CA Database (CCADB) Resources tab](https://www.ccadb.org/resources) provides lists of root certificates that are being curated for the purposes of Code Signing, Email (S/MIME), and Server Authentication (SSL/TLS)...\n\nFollowing Mozilla's advice may help with the problems like DistrustAfter creates for for projects; and CA's that are no longer in the Root CA program, like Entrust and GlobalTrust.\n","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/curl/curl/issues/comments/2643673115/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"noloader","id":3538226,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM1MzgyMjY=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3538226?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/noloader","html_url":"https://github.com/noloader","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/noloader/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/noloader/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/noloader/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/noloader/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/noloader/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/noloader/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/noloader/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/noloader/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/noloader/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/curl/curl/issues/comments/2644735713","html_url":"https://github.com/curl/curl/issues/15547#issuecomment-2644735713","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/curl/curl/issues/15547","id":2644735713,"node_id":"IC_kwDOAAiu0c6do3bh","user":{"login":"noloader","id":3538226,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM1MzgyMjY=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3538226?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/noloader","html_url":"https://github.com/noloader","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/noloader/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/noloader/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/noloader/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/noloader/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/noloader/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/noloader/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/noloader/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/noloader/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/noloader/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2025-02-08T09:08:14Z","updated_at":"2025-02-08T09:08:14Z","body":"@agwa,\n\n> Although this would cause consumers of mk-ca-bundle.pl to accept certificates that Firefox would have rejected, in practice this is not any less secure than Firefox. This is because roots with a CKA_NSS_SERVER_DISTRUST_AFTER date still have the ability to issue new certificates that are accepted by Firefox, by simply backdating the certificate's NotBefore date. \n\nI don't think the analysis is quite correct. Entrust is still issuing certificates. Firefox will reject them, while cURL will accept them, due to DistrustAfter. See <https://crt.sh/?Identity=%25&iCAID=1671>. (I think your analysis would have been more accurate if Entrust stopped issuing certificates).","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/curl/curl/issues/comments/2644735713/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_git